-- Heat Beat Grizzlies 98-91 for 13th Straight Win, Wade Scores 22
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-02T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-02/heat-beat-grizzlies-98-91-for-13th-straight-win-wade-scores-22.html
Dwyane Wade  scored 22 points as the
Miami Heat topped the Memphis Grizzlies 98-91 to record their
13th straight National Basketball Association victory.  The Heat (42-14) are second in the league, two games behind
the San Antonio Spurs (46-14).  LeBron James scored 18 points on a season-worst 4-of-14
shooting, while  Shane Battier  added 14 for the Heat, who had a
42-41 halftime advantage at AmericanAirlines Arena in Miami.  Marc Gasol scored 24 points and Zach Randolph and Mike Conley added 14 points each for the Grizzlies (38-19), who are
second in the Western Conference’s Southwest Division, 6 ½ games
behind the Spurs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
